messages.message:
My computer restarted and suddenly I am seeing this error:

```
cd /Users/eob/instabase/core-services/mount-tservice/build/go/src/instabase && GO111MODULE=on go mod init instabase
go: creating new go.mod: module instabase
docker build \
	--build-arg BASE_IMAGE_TAG=19.05.24.14.30.03 \
	-f Dockerfile.build -t instabase/mountservice-build .
ERRO[0018] failed to dial gRPC: unable to upgrade to h2c, received 502
context canceled
make: *** [build-docker] Error 1
```

has anyone seen before?
never seen, but looks like it’s a docker issue? try restarting docker?
look for an option in docker to turn off experimental features
Yeah - FWIW it seems to happen if docker daemon hasn’t finished turning on
(hence why it happened right after restart)
